I think I'm done with this,

00:03:04.710 --> 00:03:09.350
and joined Sega Sports and
started working on basketball.

00:03:09.350 --> 00:03:10.030
TODD KERPELMAN: Sounds
way more fun.

00:03:10.030 --> 00:03:12.460
WOLFF DOBSON: Which was very
much AI, although it's

00:03:12.460 --> 00:03:15.700
interesting, because so much
of the AI in console games,

00:03:15.700 --> 00:03:19.240
especially of that era, is very
much reactive planning,

00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:24.180
which is a classic theory that
came out of the University of

00:03:24.180 --> 00:03:26.370
Chicago about control.

00:03:26.370 --> 00:03:29.000
And what it really was, was this
reactive planning from

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:33.460
the early '90s, but elaborated
to the n-th degree, where we

00:03:33.460 --> 00:03:37.390
just had tons of code for every
possible situation,

00:03:37.390 --> 00:03:39.530
every frame, deciding
what should the

00:03:39.530 --> 00:03:41.160
basketball player do next?

00:03:41.160 --> 00:03:42.150
Well, is he doing this?

00:03:42.150 --> 00:03:42.790
Hes' doing this.

00:03:42.790 --> 00:03:46.170
We have hundreds of heuristics
that are all watching what--

00:03:46.170 --> 00:03:47.870
should he pass, should
he not pass?

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:50.490
If I had the ball, would I have
a better shot than if I

00:03:50.490 --> 00:03:52.740
passed it to Colt and
he had the ball?

00:03:52.740 --> 00:03:55.930
If I pass the ball to Colt,
would it get intercepted?

00:03:55.930 --> 00:03:57.926
All these things, and you're
calculating that every frame.

00:03:57.926 --> 00:03:59.050
COLT MCANLIS: If you
hand me the ball, I

00:03:59.050 --> 00:04:00.184
generally take the shot.

00:04:00.184 --> 00:04:00.940
That's how it works.

00:04:00.940 --> 00:04:01.920
WOLFF DOBSON: Well, and
then, you know--

00:04:01.920 --> 00:04:03.240
TODD KERPELMAN: Doesn't matter
where he is on the court.

00:04:03.240 --> 00:04:05.320
WOLFF DOBSON: I mean, you
actually put in emotion things

00:04:05.320 --> 00:04:07.640
like that, where it's like,
a guy like Kobe, he

00:04:07.640 --> 00:04:10.440
