00:09:18.130 --> 00:09:18.850
for his horse.

00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:21.146
And the horse came back two
levels higher or something

00:09:21.146 --> 00:09:23.230
like that, because it had killed
mice along the way, or

00:09:23.230 --> 00:09:24.660
some weird stuff.

00:09:24.660 --> 00:09:27.230
WOLFF DOBSON: That's beautiful,
and as an AI

00:09:27.230 --> 00:09:29.880
developer, I think
that's so cool.

00:09:29.880 --> 00:09:34.790
As somebody who would be
budgeting that game, I would

00:09:34.790 --> 00:09:36.900
say to myself, why did we
spend all this money on

00:09:36.900 --> 00:09:39.980
off-screen horses?

00:09:39.980 --> 00:09:42.840
If we could get three more good
horses on screen, I would

00:09:42.840 --> 00:09:46.120
