operating system.

00:30:41.660 --> 00:30:43.310
I think it's going
to make it--

00:30:43.310 --> 00:30:45.580
well, I don't exactly know
what they're doing, but I

00:30:45.580 --> 00:30:48.420
think they want to make their
own app store that is probably

00:30:48.420 --> 00:30:52.800
going to be a lot more visible
than whatever you would have

00:30:52.800 --> 00:30:53.730
to do to get to Steam.

00:30:53.730 --> 00:30:54.900
I haven't used Windows 8.

00:30:54.900 --> 00:30:55.270
I don't know.

00:30:55.270 --> 00:30:57.430
This is all just speculation.

00:30:57.430 --> 00:30:58.960
COLT MCANLIS: Also, there's
kittens everywhere.

00:30:58.960 --> 00:31:00.360
TODD KERPELMAN: But
clearly, they're

00:31:00.360 --> 00:31:02.270
saying, gee, we're awfully--

00:31:02.270 --> 00:31:03.280
WOLFF DOBSON: That's YouTube.

00:31:03.280 --> 00:31:07.030
TODD KERPELMAN: --we're
awfully tied to--

00:31:07.030 --> 00:31:10.790
they are kind of at the mercy of
one, possibly two companies

00:31:10.790 --> 00:31:14.670
that are not them, running
these platforms.

00:31:14.670 --> 00:31:16.900
WOLFF DOBSON: I just think the
other thing is that it's the

00:31:16.900 --> 00:31:18.400
continuous upgrade.

00:31:18.400 --> 00:31:21.670
I find this with car
electronics.

00:31:21.670 --> 00:31:24.850
My wife has a car that's got
a built-in Maps thing, or a

00:31:24.850 --> 00:31:29.140
built in GPS in the
radio or whatever.

00:31:29.140 --> 00:31:32.120
And my incredibly old car, I
have an aftermarket thing that

00:31:32.120 --> 00:31:33.820
I just put my Android
phone in.

00:31:33.820 --> 00:31:35.730
And every time I buy
a better Android

00:31:35.730 --> 00:31:38.020
phone, my car gets better.

00:31:38.020 --> 00:31:41.570
I think the same thing goes with
the Steam Box experience

00:31:41.570 --> 00:31:45.430
or this Big Picture experience,
which is it's been

00:31:45.430 --> 00:31:49.360
how long since the Xbox
360 came out?

00:31:49.360 --> 00:31:52.290
Waiting for these hardware
cycles for the console

00:31:52.290 --> 00:31:56.380
industry, especially where we're
at this point where 3D

00:31:56.380 --> 00:32:00.900
games with 3,000 polygons per
character look about the same

00:32:00.900 --> 00:32:04.640
as games with 7,000 polygons
per character.

00:32:04.640 --> 00:32:07.770
At that point, eh, what's
the hurry to upgrade?

00:32:07.770 --> 00:32:09.790
But if you're a hardcore gamer,
and I think Steam

00:32:09.790 --> 00:32:14.410
definitely leans into that
hardcore market, you're going

00:32:14.410 --> 00:32:16.440
to keep upgrading your PC as you
go along, which means your

00:32:16.440 --> 00:32:18.850
console going to get-- your
console, your Big Picture, is

00:32:18.850 --> 00:32:21.350
going to better and better
as you go along.

00:32:21.350 --> 00:32:23.070
TODD KERPELMAN: Well, that kind
of goes against the whole

00:32:23.070 --> 00:32:24.710
dedicated Steam Box idea.

00:32:24.710 --> 00:32:26.150
JOHN MCCUTCHAN: Yeah,
I would really--

00:32:26.150 --> 00:32:27.930
WOLFF DOBSON: But the trick
with that is that they can

00:32:27.930 --> 00:32:30.610
keep releasing Steam Box 2,
Steam Box 3, Steam Box 4, and

00:32:30.610 --> 00:32:32.386
since they're all PC games at
their heart, they're just

00:32:32.386 --> 00:32:33.570
going to keep getting better.

00:32:33.570 --> 00:32:34.910
JOHN MCCUTCHAN: Sure, but I
mean I think one of the

00:32:34.910 --> 00:32:37.680
biggest reasons why I moved
